# UI Components and Icons Guidelines

## Component Library
- **ALWAYS use shadcn/ui components** for all UI components
- Components are located in `src/components/ui/`
- Import components from `@/components/ui/[component-name]`
- Do NOT use other UI libraries (Material-UI, Ant Design, Chakra UI, etc.)
- Do NOT create custom component implementations when a shadcn/ui equivalent exists

## Icons
- **ALWAYS use icons from Lucide React library** (`lucide-react`)
- Import icons like: `import { IconName } from "lucide-react"`
- Do NOT use:
  - Unicode arrow characters (▲, ▼, →, ←, etc.)
  - Custom SVG icons
  - Other icon libraries (react-icons, @heroicons, etc.)
  - Inline SVG elements for icons
- Common icon patterns:
  - Arrows/Chevrons: `ChevronDown`, `ChevronUp`, `ChevronLeft`, `ChevronRight`, `ArrowRight`, `ArrowLeft`, `ArrowUp`, `ArrowDown`
  - Actions: `Check`, `X`, `Pencil`, `Trash`, `Edit`, `Save`, `Search`, `RefreshCw`, `Loader2`
  - Navigation: `Menu`, `Home`, `Settings`, `User`
  - Status: `Clock`, `AlertCircle`, `CheckCircle`, `XCircle`
  - Files: `Folder`, `FolderGit`, `File`, `FileText`

## Examples

### Correct Icon Usage
```tsx
import { ChevronDown, Search, X } from "lucide-react";

// Collapsible section
<Button onClick={() => setIsOpen(!isOpen)}>
  {title}
  {isOpen ? <ChevronUp className="h-4 w-4" /> : <ChevronDown className="h-4 w-4" />}
</Button>

// Search input
<div className="relative">
  <Search className="absolute left-3 top-1/2 h-4 w-4" />
  <Input className="pl-9" />
</div>

// Close button
<Button variant="ghost" size="icon">
  <X className="h-4 w-4" />
</Button>
```

### Incorrect Icon Usage (DO NOT USE)
```tsx
// ❌ Unicode characters
<span>{isOpen ? '▲' : '▼'}</span>
<span>View on GitHub →</span>

// ❌ Custom SVG
<svg xmlns="..." width="16" height="16">
  <path d="..." />
</svg>

// ❌ Other icon libraries
import { FaSearch } from "react-icons/fa";
import { ChevronDownIcon } from "@heroicons/react/24/outline";
```

## Component Structure
- Use shadcn/ui components as base building blocks
- Extend functionality by composing shadcn/ui components
- Maintain consistent styling using Tailwind CSS classes
- Follow shadcn/ui patterns for variants, sizes, and states

## When Adding New Components
1. Check if shadcn/ui has the component you need
2. If not available, check if you can compose existing shadcn/ui components
3. Only create custom components when absolutely necessary
4. Always use Lucide icons for any iconography in custom components
